abstract: The agency is trying to complete a regulation governing emissions from power sources, and a formula for how to treat nuclear plants is proving contentious.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Trying to write a complicated formula to cut carbon emissions, the Environmental Protection Agency thinks it has found a magic number: 5.8.

abstract: Racked for years by a mysterious illness, the author of “Seabiscuit” and “Unbroken” has defied the odds to write indelible works of history.
snippet: Racked for years by a mysterious illness, the author of “Seabiscuit” and “Unbroken” has defied the odds to write indelible works of history.
lead_paragraph: Late one afternoon in the summer of 2004, an aviation enthusiast named Bill Darron drove down the alley behind Laura Hillenbrand’s house in Washington. He parked his car at the rear entrance and popped open the trunk. Inside were three large boxes filled with destructive implements: bomb fuses, a flare gun, a black metal device called an intervalometer and a hulking 50-pound contraption known as a Norden bombsight.

abstract: A mother reflects on the lack of charges brought in the police killings in Ferguson, Mo., and on Staten Island, a subject that weighs on many black parents who fear for their children’s safety.
snippet: A mother reflects on the lack of charges brought in the police killings in Ferguson, Mo., and on Staten Island, a subject that weighs on many black parents who fear for their children’s safety.
lead_paragraph: We were driving to Whole Foods on a blustery evening last month when my 7-year-old son asked me the question: “Can a police officer be arrested?”

abstract: Raed Fares, a Syrian activist whose video protests skewer ISIS and President Bashar al-Assad alike, is dodging the threat of death from both sides.
snippet: Raed Fares, a Syrian activist whose video protests skewer ISIS and President Bashar al-Assad alike, is dodging the threat of death from both sides.
lead_paragraph: The overhead light in the blue Mazda 626 wasn’t working. Raed Fares, a Syrian activist whose video protests skewer ISIS and President Bashar al-Assad alike, reached up to fiddle with the light bulb before squeezing himself out of the driver’s side door. The street was in darkness. In the last few years, the Assad government cut most of the electricity (along with running water and mobile-phone service) to Kafranbel, the town in northwestern Syria where Fares lives. The only light came from an LED strip in his neighbor’s front doorway that was hooked up to a car battery. It was 12:45 a.m. on Jan. 29, 2014, and Fares, who often works until 4 a.m., had left the office early. As he fumbled to fit his key into the car’s lock, he heard the slap-slap of feet running toward him.

abstract: Jets Coach Rex Ryan and General Manager John Idzik both have the right to stake out the pragmatic high ground, if only for the purpose of their professional reputations.
snippet: Jets Coach Rex Ryan and General Manager John Idzik both have the right to stake out the pragmatic high ground, if only for the purpose of their professional reputations.
lead_paragraph: EAST RUTHERFORD, N.J. — There really ought to be a mercy rule for professional football coaches having to address the news media week after demoralizing week, a point where explanations become pointless and the whole process feels heartless.

snippet: Speaker John A. Boehner and his deputies were counting votes for a two-part plan that includes a rebuke of the president on immigration.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — House Republicans made progress on Tuesday steering some of their most conservative members away from a course that could shut down the government next week, a prospect that would badly damage the party as it prepares to take control of Congress in January.
